<h1>Cookie Policy</h1>

<h2>What are cookies?</h2>
<p>
    Cookies are small text files that websites store on the user's device (computer, tablet or
    mobile phone) when they visit them. Among other things, they enable the site to function
    correctly, to remember certain preferences or to keep the session logged in during browsing.
</p>

<h2>Which cookies does this website use?</h2>
<p>
    This website uses <strong>exclusively strictly necessary technical cookies</strong> for its
    operation. These cookies are <strong>exempt from the obligation to obtain the user's
    consent</strong>, in accordance with Article 22.2 of Ley 34/2002 (LSSI-CE) and the Guidance on
    the use of cookies of the Spanish Data Protection Agency (AEPD) (May 2024 version), as they are
    cookies indispensable for providing the service expressly requested.
</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Type</th><th>Duration</th><th>Consent</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>.AspNetCore.Culture</code></td>
            <td>To remember the language selected by the user in order to display the site in that language.</td>
            <td>Technical</td>
            <td>Persistent</td>
            <td>Exempt (Art. 22.2 LSSI)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Session cookie (ASP.NET Core Identity)</td>
            <td>To keep the session logged in and authenticated during browsing in the areas that require it.</td>
            <td>Technical / session</td>
            <td>Session</td>
            <td>Exempt (Art. 22.2 LSSI)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Antiforgery cookie (antiforgery / CSRF)</td>
            <td>To protect forms against cross-site request forgery (CSRF) attacks, ensuring the security of submissions.</td>
            <td>Technical / security</td>
            <td>Session</td>
            <td>Exempt (Art. 22.2 LSSI)</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>No analytics, advertising or third-party cookies are used</h2>
<p>
    This website <strong>does not use analytics or audience-measurement cookies, nor advertising
    or tracking cookies, nor third-party cookies</strong>. As only technical cookies exempt from
    consent are used, <strong>no cookie banner is displayed</strong>, since there is no processing
    that requires the user's prior consent.
</p>

<h2>How to manage or delete cookies?</h2>
<p>
    Although the cookies used are necessary for the operation of the site, you can configure your
    browser to block or delete cookies at any time. Please note that disabling technical cookies
    may prevent certain parts of the site from working correctly (for example, logging in or
    submitting forms).
</p>
<p>You can find out how to do this in your browser's help section:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data.</li>
    <li><strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Cookies and Site Data.</li>
    <li><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions.</li>
    <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy.</li>
</ul>

